We were surveying birds in the Sirumalai hills when we heard this call. The call came from a distance of 200metres from us and then it came closer and passed us. However we could not see the bird. It seemed to be a duet between two birds. But we are unsure about this. The duet went on for around 15minutes and more as the birds were on the move. 

The habitat was of sparse trees and dense undergrowth of grasses.
